<br>
- Midgard and the end regen/left axe situation will be hit by the nerf bat<br>
- Hibernia will get love<br>
<br>
While I have mixed feelings about the possible incoming nerf (yes, it is powerful, but I just finished a 3h siege at bledmeer, and I don't see how it is more powerful than enchanters/animists/other hib casters in the right situation, but I digress), the probable end result will be, like it was the case every time Mythic made such adjustments to the game, very, very bleak days ahead for Midgard, as the masses will jump into the next bandwagon.<br>
<br>
IMHO, if Mythic want to take this approach (nerf mid &quot;overpowered&quot; classes, boost hib after boosting albion), it is of the UTMOST importance that the (lot of) midgard classes and specs that ... ahem... don't perform that well in RvR, get some intention too.<br>
<br>
The few powerful classes combos don't have to hide the problems many midgard players are facing.<br>
Around 4% (four) of the active Guinevere RvR Midgard population is made of warriors. Aye, warriors, in the realm created from the tales of the viking folk. The skald has been neglected since the beta phase. Thanes, Hunters, Spiritmasters ...<br>
When will the gods have a look at our poor weapon styles (look at the &quot;go axe if you don't want to gimp yourself&quot; thread). When will fighting with a two handed weapon will be a real option for all the melee classes (except the skald, but by default ...) in our realm ?<br>
<br>
Nerf left axe if you must, but there is another reason why everyone reroll a zerker/SB/shaman nowadays ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/8/03 9:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Producer's letter</span><hr size=1> 2H Savage. <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 2:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aye</span><hr size=1> Aye, forgot about that one. I am pretty surprised actually to see left axe singled out this way. With savages, we have a truly overpowered class.<br>
<br>
But my point doesn't change. The fact that a small subset of classes are very powerful (or overpowered) in Midgard, or in any realm for that matter, doesn't have to prevent their less fortunate brothers to get their much needed attention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=albron>Albron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 5:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tyrantsonline.com/albron.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aye</span><hr size=1> Its ironic but the &quot;most overpowered class in the game&quot; (as so many like to call us) ARE NOT getting nerfed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Midgard NEEDS things like the LA/quad hitting savage with end regen as well as AE stun and PBAE to compete.  Yeah, its a huge advantage but look at our POS RAs and hybrids classes. <p>Albron<br>
Level 50 Norse Skald<br>
HOOKED on speed!<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daocoverlords>daoc overlords</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 6:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://daoc-overlords.home.attbi.com/crazyivan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aye</span><hr size=1> This may not be a nerf just to Zerkers and Shadowblades. If Mythic follows the recommendations of some of the whiners on the VNBoards, WE will get nerfed as well...<br>
<br>
How? Well, many--including Mythic--have said that it's not the LA styles alone that are &quot;overpowering&quot; Zerkers and Shadowblades, it's those high endurance cost styles in conjuction with Endurance that doesn't fade. So... what if Mythic tones down the END buff instead?<br>
<br>
At that point, it's the hybrid classes that really will suffer. Look, without styles our damage output can't compare with stronger classes. But those styles chew up End like crazy. If we no longer have end buff--or a weaker version of it--then we're stuck with a couple good shots (and pray you don't miss on a high end cost style) until end runs out, and then it's back to tink...tink...tink...Alb Tank: &quot;Do I have a low level DoT on me? Oh, it's just a Skald hitting me. LOL!&quot;  And no, the crappy, bugged pulse-dropping damage add doesn't make up for that loss of style damage.<br>
<br>
And what will that do to Speed, the one thing our class is valued for in Midgard?  Well, factor this into the equation: a group with a Skald's speed 5, LW1, and the end buff could permasprint, giving them a slightly better measure of speed--helping to make up for the dropped pulses from speed, thus allowing our groups to compete in speed with Hib/Alb groups who's speed doesn't drop pulses: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=48123685&replies=10">vnboards.ign.com/message....replies=10</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ...take that end away, and the realm becomes slower, too. And of course, those who've purchased LW will be SOL. Without and End buff, LW1 has negligible impact on sprinting.<br>
<br>
It's going to bear watching closely how Mythic wields the infamous nerf bat, to ensure that they don't manage to nerf the entire realm just to compensate for the perceived &quot;overpowering&quot; of our Zerkers and Shadowzerks.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Raido Stormrider, level 43 Skald, Mithril Circle on Galahad<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 7:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, I have always believed the speed pulse problem was common to all speed classes, but the instrument explaination make sense ... Rosey, is this true or not ?<br>
<br>
I am not too worried about the perma sprint thing. It should be nerfed, honestly ... but we must get speed of sound and our pulses must be fixed fixed.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 7:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aye</span><hr size=1> At the risk of sounding like a VN poster, if Mythic is going to choose this path of advancement, I will most likely be cancelling my account.  My reasoning?<br>
<br>
&lt;rant on&gt;<br>
<br>
1)  Hibs are getting &quot;assessed&quot;, mids are getting nerfed.  Did they just skip the assessment phase for the mids?<br>
<br>
2)  A class that has ~200 lvl50's (valewalkers, animists) game wide and has only been in the game 4 months gets a look before a class that has 3000+ and has been ingame since launch.  Obviously Mythic has no understanding of economics and how demographics create demand.<br>
<br>
3) Speaking of population, there was no mention of fixing population imbalance.  IMO, a problem worse than anything else in the game right now.<br>
<br>
4)  Don't get me wrong, I think hibs need buffing, but in order to be fair, they really should have assessed all realms at once.  They didn't, and based on past schedule it will probably be 3+ months before midgard even gets a look.  In the meantime, Mids get a nerf to try to overcome.<br>
<br>
5)  Mids are in a lose/lose situation.  If they nerf LA, Mids now have NO other class that can do the dmg output of other realms tanks**.  If they nerf End Regen, everyone who put points into Longwind might have wasted them if it disables perma-sprint.<br>
<br>
6)  Buffing LW and CD....great, Nightshades and Inf's will be even more powerful.<br>
<br>
7)  A press release required for RvR?? How much do you wanna bet we are going to be asked to buy something.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry to harp on it, but going back to zerkers, what ever happened to other realms learning how to overcome?<br>
<br>
All the left axe and end regen in the world won't help a rooted zerker. Or just in case that zerker purged root - shield slam. Two purely effective counters against the dreaded zerker. Yet there is no counter against things like BoF, SoS, TWF, BAoD... <br>
<br>
Basically you've got a ton of people whining about how horrific the damage is from zerkers, when air theurgs are doing 450+ damage every 1.5 seconds from range through 40% resists regardless of armor type.<br>
<br>
Like I said, I completely disagree with this course of action, and I will do my best to show it to Mythic if they push forward.  Again I apologize if I sound like the typical VN whiner, but even after a night's sleep, i'm still pretty steamed about it.<br>
<br>
Sideshow lvl50 Skald<br>
Palomides <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daocoverlords>daoc overlords</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 8:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://daoc-overlords.home.attbi.com/crazyivan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aye</span><hr size=1> Someone just posted the smartest idea I've heard yet on how to bring Zerkers and SZ's into balance...<br>
<br>
...fix DEFENSE. It wouldn't be an issue if in RvR other classes could block and parry more consistently.<br>
<br>
Q <p>Raido Stormrider, level 43 Skald, Mithril Circle on Galahad<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=t0a5t>t0a5t</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 10:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> defense</span><hr size=1> You know if they fixed Block/Parry in RvR it would effectively emasculate Skalds, Polearmsman, LW users &amp; Friars..<br>
<br>
Errr on second thought, FIX DEFENSE!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 12:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: defense</span><hr size=1> As far as I have heard from the other music classes, pulsed songs all drop randomly and erratically.<br>
<br>
That was one of the reasons that when they added duration/frequency and made them different recently, they were trying to find out if it made any difference in the dropped pulses.  It didn't.<br>
<br>
Rosey<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 257<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/10/03 3:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Defense</span><hr size=1> I do agree Mythic must fix defense.<br>
<br>
However, even if we will benefit from a parry increase, it still will be an additional nail on the skald's coffin. <br>
It will arguably give us a bit of help against assassins and minstrels/wardens.<br>
But all pure tanks, and all other &quot;hybrids&quot; will benefit much more, due to their 2.0 spec and/or possibility to spec in shield.<br>
Overall, we will just lose ground again in relative power against all other melee classes.<br>
<br>
So, yes, defense should be fixed. The code is buggy, some penalties are completely arbitrary and must go away.<br>
